    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-09-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/122–123.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President of Mexico</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Upon receipt of your telegram of the 20th, my proposed message was sent on the
                    21st to each of the five Central American Presidents. I share Your Excellency’s
                    satisfaction that the Central American <pb facs="0799" n="649" xml:id="pg_649"/>
                    situation has assumed so hopeful an attitude, and I trust our joint efforts may
                    successfully conduce to lasting peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore Roosevelt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
